More accurate wording
It should be made clear that Islamic beliefs precede and lay the foundation for the extremism, not that the extremism comes first and Islamic beliefs are later adopted as justification.

Criticism of the use of the phrase belongs in sections for criticism, We don't need a childish back and forth about how people of different viewpoints have reacted to the term at the top of the article. Also interesting that the phrase "Western political speech" is used, which is POV. "Islamic Terrorism" is the phrase used by the majority of the world's population, not just in the Western world (which itself is not at all homogenous).

[[WP:CLARITY]], should make the significant point that these Uyghurs are Al-Qaeda connected terrorist fighters actively involved in the [[War in Syria]] and are not refugees, a normal expat community nor members of a benign political party.

Arab is not a single ethnic group, it is like the term "white" - covering a large number of semitic language speaking ethnicities throughout the Islamic world. Being of Berber ancestry (and also for some Nafricans due to Vandals and colonial influence Western European ancestry) does not make North African Arabs any less Arab. There are Arab tribes who are very different in ancestry, and why specifically single out genetic Berbers from their Arab identity in this case?
